## Architecture
This project uses a layered architecture with strict dependency direction (inward only):

1. Presentation/API Layer — Handles HTTP requests, CLI commands, or UI. Depends on Service only.
2. Service/Business Logic Layer — Core business rules and orchestration. Depends on Data only.
3. Data/Repository Layer — Persistence and external data access. Depends on Shared only.
4. Shared/Core — Types, utilities, constants. No dependencies on other layers.

Refer to `architecture.json` in the project root for machine-readable boundary definitions.

## Code Style
- Use meaningful, descriptive names for all identifiers.
- Keep functions small and single-purpose.
- Prefer composition over inheritance.
- Handle errors at boundaries where you have context to act.
- Use typed/structured errors, not raw strings.
- No `any` types (TypeScript) or untyped parameters (Python).

## Key Commands
- Build: `{{BUILD_COMMAND}}`
